  "detailedRequirements": "<p dir=\"ltr\">This is another challenge in the series for Cloud Hub, where we want to improve on our setup of Griddle-React. These improvements will require updates to both our API and react web application. On the API we need to need to add support for sorting the applications and users. For the application we want to add infinite scrolling and update sorting to sort all of the records, just not the initial set.<br />\n&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">App Requirements</span></span></strong></p>\n\n<p>1. Implement a handler for the Griddle-React `externalChangeSort` property that calls the existing Redux action handler with the currently sorted column.</p>\n\n<p>2. Make sure to implement helper functions to pass from the page components down to the ListPage child - keeping state managed in one place (the parent page component connected to the store). &nbsp;<span>see <a href=\"https://facebook.github.io/react/docs/multiple-components.html\">React Documentation</a></span></p>\n\n<p>3. add sort parameter (sortColumn) to fetchApplications or fetchEmployees that specifies the column name and the direction of sort using this format: &quot;+columnName&quot; or &quot;-columnName&quot; or &ldquo;+columnOneName&rdquo;</p>\n\n<p>4. implement infinite scroll for Applications and Employees pages using Griddle-React</p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">API Requirements</span></span></strong></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">1. add in sorting functionality on the API level to handle ascending/descending sorts for each column in Applications and Users</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">2. API should be able to handling sorting for multiple fields .. e.g. &quot;+columnOneName, -columnTwoName&quot;</span></span></p>\n\n<p><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">3. update offset on GET calls for Applications and Users - from 10 to 25</span><br />\n<span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">4. Changes must not break any tests `npm run test`</span></span></p>\n\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong><span><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial; font-size:14.6667px\">General Requirements</span></span></strong></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">1. Default sorts should be appName for Applications and lastName for Users/Employees</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">2. All added JavaScript must pass the included eslint specifications (see Airbnb&#39;s Style Guide for more information) - run &quot;npm run lint&quot; to test</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-size:14px\"><span style=\"background-color:transparent; color:rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family:arial\">3. ES6 syntax is preferred, as Babel has been setup to handle transpiling the syntax to the current JavaScript standard.</span></span></p>\n\n<p dir=\"ltr\">&nbsp;</p>\n",
  "digitalRunPoints": null,
